{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry includes SURF1 and Shy1 proteins. The surfeit locus 1 gene (SURF1 or surf-1) encodes a conserved protein of about 300 amino-acid residues that seems to be involved in the biogenesis of cytochrome c oxidase [[cite:PUB00003909]]. Vertebrate SURF1 is evolutionary related to yeast protein Shy1, which is a mitochondrial inner membrane protein required for assembly of cytochrome c oxidase [[cite:PUB00062912]]. There seems to be two transmembrane regions in these proteins, one in the N-terminal, the other in the C-terminal.</p>\n\n<p>Defects in SURF1 are a cause of Leigh syndrome (LS). LS is a severe neurological disorder characterised by bilaterally symmetrical necrotic lesions in subcortical brain regions that is commonly associated with systemic cytochrome c oxidase (COX) deficiency [[cite:PUB00003909], [cite:PUB00062910], [cite:PUB00062911]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false} {"text" "<p>The surfeit locus gene SURF4 (or surf-4) encodes a conserved integral eukaryotic membrane protein of about 270 to 300 amino-acid residues that seems to be located in the endoplasmic reticulum [[cite:PUB00003783]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR23427" "SURFEIT LOCUS PROTEIN"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Surfeit locus 1/4", "short" "Surf1/Surf4"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 5, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 6586, "taxa" 22092, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 25276, "sets" 0, "proteins" 25276, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 18603}, "pathways" 19}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR045214", :literature {"PUB00003909" {"URL" nil, "issue" "4", "authors" ["Zhu Z" "Yao J" "Johns T" "Fu K" "De Bie I" "Macmillan C" "Cuthbert AP" "Newbold RF" "Wang J" "Chevrette M" "Brown 